7Sep06 - Have been checking this position for quite a while now.  a3 is protected by no less than 4 pieces. The idea behind Na7 is to relocate it to b5 where it is attacking the pawns on a3 and c3. However, before that I should prevent the pawn from reaching a4 by Ba4, attacking the queen in the process.

01Nov06 - Freeing up the rook to come to a8 if needed. Whites queenside is looking very cluttered. Possibly the critical position. White has some possibilities, his queen is quite free. There are no attacks on his king. Blacks knight on f5 does not really have many escape options and the f7 pawn could become weak later. For now it is an all out attack of whites pieces!

20Nov06 - if white takes then b3 pawn then 29. ... Nc4 attacking the queen and also allowing Rxa1 possibilities. If 29. c4 then 29. ... Nxc4 forking the rook and the queen. Maybe the best possibility for white is 29. Nxd5? White is now thinking for time over this move.
